    <text>
        <body>
            <div xml:id="d.1">
                <head type="title">Miklós Oláh to a friend (Brussels, 8 September 1532)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p xml:id="reg.p.1">Although he has often experienced his friend’s
                            benevolence towards him, now he especially experienced it from Joannes,
                            whom his friend had sent. Joannes told him in praise what a building his
                            friend has been building for a month now. He would be happy if he could
                            see the house and admire his talent in architecture as well.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb facs="https://www.eleveltar.hu/kereso-portlet/spring/digitalcontent/getcontent/preservica/F7F8B70A-1C56-48C4-8DDD-FC0CE3C5C2AD
                    "/>
                <p xml:id="p.1">Ad amicum.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.2">Quamvis multis ex causis tuam in me benevolentiam singularem
                    cognoverim, tamen nunc maxime cognovi ex sermonibus tuis
                        <persName>Ioannis</persName>,<note xml:id="note.1">We do not know him more
                        closely but he might be Joannes Ruthenus, see Ep.
                            273.<ref>olahus.tei.15320920_1</ref></note> quem nuper ad me miseras, </p>
                <pb facs="https://www.eleveltar.hu/kereso-portlet/spring/digitalcontent/getcontent/preservica/860DBA6F-80E8-4DCD-8CF4-31135AFF41EE
                    "/>
                <p xml:id="p.3">quis multis <del corresp="editor">multis</del> mihi declaravit, quo
                    in me animo esses, et qua diligentia omnes meas res curaveris. Non est igitur,
                    cur multum in tuo erga me amore dubitem, qui mihi certior semper fuit et
                    praesentior, quam ego aut cogitare, aut optare potuissem. Idem tuus
                        <persName>Ioannes</persName> miris laudibus tua quoque aedificia mihi
                    extulit, quae tu iam a mense aedificare coepisti. Scio te multa in ea re
                    insumpsisse, et plura adhuc ut voluntatem tuam expleas insumpturum. Quae minima
                    omnia esse videbuntur, si aedificia voti tuo respondebunt. Quae quidem ego si
                    videre possem, viderer esse fortunatus, ut ex ipsis aedificiis, tuum aedificandi
                    ingenium cognoscerem, dabitur tamen, ut spero, tempus, ut et te et tuas domos
                    videre possim. Vale.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.4"><placeName>Bruxellae</placeName> 8. Septembris 1532.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
